      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Hmm, what makes the fuzz target produce valid blocks, but not valid transactions? Is it that the prevhash can be solved by a fuzz engine for some reason, but the prevout can not? I guess that could be, because one may be a linear memory compare, and the other a map lookup?\r\n\r\nNot sure what to do here, but an alternative could be to add the mempool reset logic and hope that fuzz engines in the future will be smart enough to solve a map lookup?",
